This block of logic should really be out in the Module layer. It's more to do with the internal workings of oEQ as opposed to how we present a result.
const buildSelectionSessionItemSummaryLink =
  ({ stateId, integId, layout }: SelectionSessionInfo,
  indexNumber?: number, totalCount?: number): string => {
    ...
}
If you had something like that, then this method could be more (declarative) like:
const itemLink = () => {
  const itemTitle = name ? highlightField(name) : uuid;
  const basicLink = <Link to={routes.ViewItem.to(uuid, version)}>{itemTitle}</Link>;
  return renderData?.selectionSessionInfo ?
    (<MUILink
      href={buildSelectionSessionItemSummaryLink(renderData.selectionSessionInfo)}
      underline="none">
        {itemTitle}
    </MUILink>) :
    basicLink;
}
Added bonus, would be that you can then also easily unit test this.

